<section class="hero">
  <canvas class="stars" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
  <div class="wrap hero-inner">
    <span class="eyebrow">Blockyfy Tools</span>
    <h1>BLOCKY <span class="glow">STUDIO</span></h1>
    <p class="lede">The desktop studio for Minecraft structures and worldgen. Design in code or in the editor, orbit your build in 3D, lint it for quality and export it anywhere.</p>
    <div class="badges">
      <span class="badge">Windows desktop</span>
      <span class="badge">.nbt · .schem · .litematic · .bbmodel</span>
      <span class="badge hot">Private preview</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn" href="#download">Get the app</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#support">Support development</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="features">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Features</span>
      <h2>From idea to in-game, fast</h2>
      <p>Born inside the Dragon Block Galactic pipeline and battle-tested on real builds before it ever became a product.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid cols-3">
      <div class="card reveal">
        <h3><span class="ico">🧱</span> Voxel engine</h3>
        <p>A sparse voxel canvas with parametric shapes, deterministic palettes and vanilla-faithful baking of stairs, fences and connections.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <h3><span class="ico">🌀</span> 3D preview</h3>
        <p>Orbit your structure in a live viewer with layer slicing, plus rendered elevations, cutaways and contact sheets for quick review.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <h3><span class="ico">🎨</span> Palette browser</h3>
        <p>Browse 800+ blocks with color swatches, search and filters. Click to copy ids or assemble weighted palettes visually.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <h3><span class="ico">⛰</span> Worldgen tools</h3>
        <p>Heightmaps, strata, water, scatter rules and placement constraints, with automatic region previews of the generated terrain.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <h3><span class="ico">🔁</span> Interop everywhere</h3>
        <p>Import and export .nbt, .schem and .litematic, plus .bbmodel export that opens natively in Blockbench. Multi-version palettes from 1.20.1 to 1.21.5.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <h3><span class="ico">🤖</span> Built for AI workflows</h3>
        <p>A headless CLI and an MCP server let AI assistants design, lint and iterate on structures with you, with quality checks built in.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section alt" id="download">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="band reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Download</span>
      <h2>Currently in private preview</h2>
      <p>Blocky Studio is being polished with a small group of builders before the public release. Supporters get preview builds first.</p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <button class="btn soon" disabled title="Public download not open yet">Download for Windows</button>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#support">Get preview access</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="support">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Supporter program</span>
      <h2>Help us build the builder</h2>
      <p>Supporting funds development and puts every new build in your hands before anyone else.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tiers reveal" data-tiers="blocky-studio"></div>
    <p class="tiers-note"><span class="lock">🔒</span> Secure checkout by Stripe. Cancel anytime from the customer portal.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section alt" id="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
      <h2>Questions, answered</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq reveal">
      <details>
        <summary>What platforms are supported?</summary>
        <p>Windows today, as a lightweight desktop app with a one-click installer that does not require admin rights.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Does it work with my mod's custom blocks?</summary>
        <p>Yes. A simple project config teaches the studio any modded block registry, and new blocks flow into palettes and previews automatically.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What does "built for AI" mean?</summary>
        <p>Blocky Studio exposes its whole engine through a CLI and an MCP server. AI assistants like Claude can create, validate and refine structures in your project while you review everything in the 3D viewer.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I cancel my support anytime?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Subscriptions are managed through a secure Stripe customer portal where you can cancel or change your tier in one click.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

